## 7. Recommended Remediation (NOT YET APPLIED)

To untrack these files while keeping them on disk:

```bash
git rm --cached skool_dump.txt strategies_dump.txt hedge_fund_dump.txt hmm_dump.txt debugging_dump.txt
git rm --cached data_parquet1.zip data_parquet2.zip claude-skills.zip
git commit -m "chore: untrack private course dumps and large zip files"
```

The `--cached` flag removes the file from git's index but keeps it on disk.
The existing `.gitignore` rules will prevent them from being re-added.

**Note:** This does NOT remove the files from git history. If these files
were ever pushed to a remote, they remain in the history. A full purge
(`git filter-repo` or BFG) would be needed to scrub history — but that is
a destructive operation and should only be done with explicit approval.

